1. CDS Data Model Annotations

Used in CDS view entities to define data exposure, access control, and OData behavior.

Annotation	Purpose / Description
@AbapCatalog.sqlViewName	Defines the technical SQL view name (for DDIC).
@AbapCatalog.compiler.compareFilter	Optimizes view performance for filters.
@EndUserText.label	Provides a human-readable label for the CDS entity.
@AccessControl.authorizationCheck: #CHECK	Enables authorization via CDS role objects (DCL).
@Metadata.ignorePropagatedAnnotations	Ignores propagated metadata from associations.
@ObjectModel.modelCategory	Defines if it‚Äôs a business object or analytical view.
@ObjectModel.representativeKey	Defines key fields representing the entity.
@ObjectModel.transactionalProcessingEnabled: true	Allows transactional operations (create, update, delete).
@ObjectModel.createEnabled: true	Enables create operation for the entity.
@ObjectModel.updateEnabled: true	Enables update operation for the entity.
@ObjectModel.deleteEnabled: true	Enables delete operation for the entity.
@ObjectModel.readOnly: true	Marks the entity as read-only.
@ObjectModel.text.association	Links an entity field to a text table for description.
@ObjectModel.foreignKey.association	Defines a foreign key relationship.
@OData.publish: true	Publishes the entity as an OData service automatically.
@OData.entitySet.name	Sets a custom OData entity set name.
@Semantics.amount.currencyCode	Marks a currency relationship for amount fields.
@Semantics.quantity.unitOfMeasure	Marks a UoM relationship for quantity fields.
@Search.defaultSearchElement: true	Marks a field as searchable in Fiori UI.
@Search.fuzzinessThreshold	Configures fuzzy search tolerance.
‚öôÔ∏è 2. Behavior Definition (BDEF) Annotations

Used in the behavior definition file to describe how the entity behaves (CRUD, locking, draft, etc.)

Annotation / Keyword	Purpose / Description
managed / unmanaged	Defines whether the RAP BO is handled automatically (managed) or manually (unmanaged).
implementation in class zbp_...	Links to the ABAP behavior pool class.
strict (2)	Enforces stricter RAP syntax rules (recommended).
lock master	Activates automatic locking for the root entity.
authorization master (instance)	Enables authorization handling at instance level.
etag master	Enables optimistic locking and concurrency control.
create; update; delete;	Declares supported CRUD operations.
association _<assoc_name>	Allows operations on related entities.
draft;	Enables draft handling for the BO.
validation	Adds custom data validation logic.
determination	Triggers automatic data enrichment logic.
mapping for	Maps fields between CDS and persistence.
field (readonly)	Makes a field read-only in the behavior context.
field (mandatory)	Requires a value on create/update.
field (update)	Allows updating the field during modify.
action <action_name>	Defines custom actions for the BO.
static action	Declares an action not tied to a specific instance.
üé® 3. UI Annotations (Fiori Elements)

Used to define how data appears in Fiori apps ‚Äî list reports, object pages, etc.

Annotation	Purpose / Description
@UI.headerInfo	Defines the object title and subtitle in the header area.
@UI.facet	Creates sections (tabs, forms) in the Fiori Object Page.
@UI.lineItem	Defines columns in the List Report table.
@UI.identification	Defines fields in the Object Page (main form).
@UI.selectionField	Defines filter fields for the list report.
@UI.dataPoint	Displays KPI or key data value.
@UI.chart	Configures chart representation (type, measures, dimensions).
@UI.fieldGroup	Groups fields together in UI forms.
@UI.hidden: true	Hides the field from the Fiori view.
@UI.textArrangement	Defines whether code/text or text/code is displayed.
@UI.importance	Sets field visibility level (HIGH, MEDIUM, LOW).
@UI.createHidden	Hides field during creation.
üîê 4. Authorization & Control Annotations
Annotation	Purpose / Description
@AccessControl.authorizationCheck: #CHECK	Enforces CDS access control (DCL).
@AccessControl.personalData.blocking	Used in GDPR scenarios to block personal data.
@AbapCatalog.buffering.allow	Enables table/view buffering.
@AbapCatalog.buffering.numberOfKeyFields	Defines key fields for buffering.
@ObjectModel.transactionalProcessingDelegated	Delegates transactional handling to another BO.
@ObjectModel.dataCategory	Defines type of data model (transactional, analytical, master).
üåê 5. Service Definition / Binding Annotations
Annotation	Purpose / Description
@OData.publish: true	Automatically generates an OData service.
@EndUserText.label	Descriptive text for OData entity.
@Metadata.allowExtensions: true	Allows metadata extension for the entity.
@Consumption.derivation: {}	Defines derivation rules for consumption views.
@Metadata.allowExtensions: true	Enables extension by partners or customers.
üß† Example: RAP with Key Annotations
@EndUserText.label: 'Customer Entity'
@AccessControl.authorizationCheck: #CHECK
@ObjectModel.transactionalProcessingEnabled: true
@OData.publish: true
@UI.headerInfo: { typeName: 'Customer', title: { value: 'CustomerName' } }
@UI.lineItem: [ { position: 10, value: 'CustomerName', label: 'Customer' },
                { position: 20, value: 'City', label: 'City' } ]
define view entity ZC_Customer as select from kna1 {
  key kunnr as CustomerID,
  name1 as CustomerName,
  ort01 as City,
  land1 as Country
}

üßæ Summary Table by Layer
Layer	Example Annotations	Purpose
CDS / Data Model	@OData.publish, @ObjectModel.*, @EndUserText.label	Define structure and expose data
Behavior Definition	create; update; delete;, field (readonly), lock master	Define logic and transactional behavior
UI (Fiori)	@UI.lineItem, @UI.headerInfo, @UI.selectionField	Define look & feel for Fiori Elements
Security / Access	@AccessControl.authorizationCheck	Enable DCL-based authorization
Service Binding	@OData.publish	Expose as REST/OData service
